<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Turbocharger - Installation -
        High Torque Turbocharger
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="4">
        <title>High Torque Turbocharger</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Use anti-sieze compound on the mounting bolts and all other bolt threads used on the exhaust
                    system to prevent high temperature corrosion.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pre-assemble the right and left side tube assemblies to the exhaust inlet adapter with the
                exhaust flange gasket (either side up) mounted between the exhaust tube flange and the exhaust inlet
                adapter. Torque the exhaust inlet adapter flange bolts that secure the exhaust tubes to the exhaust
                inlet adapter to the special torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200275" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8028A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger Exhaust Tube Mounting Hardware (Right Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Mounting Nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the reassembled exhaust inlet adapter and tube assembly into position and secure the
                exhaust tube assembly to the left and right exhaust manifolds. Finger tighten the mounting hardware.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove all protective caps or duct tape from the turbocharger, pedestal and crankcase
                openings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200239" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3303.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger Oil Supply O-Ring and Oil Drain O-Ring</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Supply O-Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Drain O-Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Mounting Pad</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a light coat of grease to a new oil drain O-ring and oil supply O-ring. Install the
                O-rings into the turbocharger mounting pad.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the turbocharger pedestal on the crankcase. Make sure the bolt holes in the pedestal
                align with the bolt holes in the crankcase. Install and tighten the flange head mounting bolts to the
                standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new oil supply and oil drain O-rings on the top of the pedestal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align oil supply and drain ports and place turbocharger on the pedestal. Install the two
                mounting bolts and tighten them to the special torque valve.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the seal and align the exhaust inlet adapter with the turbine inlet. Install the
                V-band clamp and tighten to the special torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the exhaust tube mounting hardware at the exhaust manifolds to the special torque
                value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200277" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9128.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing Charge Air Cooling Tube/Crossover Pipe Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crossover Pipe</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Charge Air Cooling Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose Clamps (4)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Intake Manifold Hoses (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use clean engine oil to lubricate a new turbocharger compressor outlet seal. Install the
                seal into the compressor housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the charge air cooling tube/crossover pipe assembly as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the charge air cooling tube/crossover pipe assembly to the turbocharger
                    compressor housing and intake manifold hoses.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">To secure the charge air cooling tube to the turbocharger compressor housing, tighten
                    the turbocharger compressor outlet clamp.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten the four hose clamps (two per side) to secure the intake manifold hoses to the
                    air intake manifold covers.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the air inlet elbow and clamp. Tighten the clamp.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure>
            <graphic filename="../figf15/F1519.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="532px"/>
            <caption>Installing Road Draft Tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Road Draft Tube Mounting Bolts</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the road draft tube into the correct position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the road draft tube mounting bolts in the crankcase. Tighten the bolts to the
                standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
